    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-24T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-24T18:00:00-05:00" n="576"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d576">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.24546/39: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Wellington</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cox</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Wellington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-25T11:00:00+12:00"
                            >November 25, 1941—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 25—6:57 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department’s November 22, 4 p.m. Prime Minister states that the New Zealand
                    Government understands and agrees to this matter.</p>
                <p>He has asked me to express his gratification for the message contained in your
                    November 13, 11 p.m.<note n="16" xml:id="d576fn16">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cox</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
